# Lumiverb — CLI Rules

## The CLI is an API Client Only
- The CLI never touches the tenant DB, Quickwit, or object storage directly.
- Every operation goes through the API (`/v1/`).
- The only local state the CLI maintains is a SQLite asset-map cache (SHA256 dedup) —
  this is the one permitted SQLite use in the entire codebase.

## Proxy & Thumbnail Generation (happens locally before upload)
- Proxy: JPEG, max 2048px longest side, quality 85, sRGB, generated in-memory (never written to disk as an intermediate).
- Thumbnail: JPEG, max 400px, quality 80, in-memory.
- SHA256 dedup: check local SQLite cache before uploading — skip if already known to server.
- Source files never leave the local machine.

## Command Design
- All commands log at INFO level by default. No `--verbose` or `--quiet` flags.
- All polling/scanning commands must have a `--once` flag.
- Polling loops sleep no more than 5 seconds.
- CTRL+C exits cleanly with code 0.
- Always show full `uv run lumiverb ...` commands in help text and docs.

